"population on an annual basis since 2000 should be provided, expressed in"
" thousands. Demographic data is pre-filled in the reporting table CP-1.T2"
" using data from the WorldPop dataset from 2000 to 2023. Parties should "
"note that this dataset has not been updated for the 2026 reporting and "
"therefore the final three years (2021, 2022, and 2023) duplicate values "
"for 2020. Moreover it should be noted that while the School of Geography "
"and Environmental Science at the University of Southampton (UK) has "
"recently released a new global demographic dataset for 2015–2030, it was "
"still in beta format at the time the 2026 reporting process was launched "
"and will not be made available as default data. Beta versions of datasets"
" can contain inconsistencies, errors or anomalies. As soon as this new "
"global demographic dataset is formally published, Parties will be able to"
